1
00:00:05,076 --> 00:00:13,150
Śrīla Gurudev said to me once, 
and it’s forever ringing in my ears,

2
00:00:13,150 --> 00:00:19,560
and with him,
sitting on his veranda in Calcutta,

3
00:00:19,560 --> 00:00:28,826
and beneath the framed śloka 
of Śikṣāṣṭakam of Mahāprabhu:

4
00:00:28,894 --> 00:00:37,549
tṛṇād api sunīchena taror iva sahiṣṇunā
amāninā mānadena kīrtanīyaḥ sadā hariḥ

5
00:00:37,839 --> 00:00:40,929
[“My Religion Is Finding Fault Within Myself”]

6
00:00:41,039 --> 00:00:49,847
So many times he invoked 
the substance of this śloka:

7
00:00:49,847 --> 00:00:53,907
humility, being humble—

8
00:00:53,907 --> 00:01:00,469
more humble than a blade of grass,
more tolerant than a tree,

9
00:01:00,637 --> 00:01:07,387
and giving honor to others 
without expecting any honor in return.

10
00:01:07,467 --> 00:01:13,377
And on this particular occasion 
he said,

11
00:01:13,377 --> 00:01:18,167
“My religion is finding fault 
with myself.”

12
00:01:20,247 --> 00:01:24,987
A very simple, succinct, 
and profound statement.

13
00:01:24,987 --> 00:01:30,083
“My religion is finding fault 
with myself.”

14
00:01:30,083 --> 00:01:33,803
This is the path 
to self‒improvement.

15
00:01:33,803 --> 00:01:40,256
By looking outward 
into the environment,

16
00:01:40,274 --> 00:01:45,274
casting blame on the environment
or other people,

17
00:01:45,274 --> 00:01:54,794
the actors within that environment,
circumstances.

18
00:01:54,794 --> 00:02:03,061
All of these excuses 
that we can make

19
00:02:03,061 --> 00:02:06,511
for adopting something less 
than proper behavior.

20
00:02:06,528 --> 00:02:15,978
The excuses that we can make
for not practicing Vaiṣṇava religion.

21
00:02:15,978 --> 00:02:21,554
Which Gurudev summed up in that 
“My religion is finding fault from myself”,

22
00:02:21,554 --> 00:02:25,774
and alluding to what 
is expressed by Mahāprabhu.

23
00:02:27,427 --> 00:02:33,963
And sometimes Śrīla Gurudev would say 
on the “amāninā mānadena” aspect,

24
00:02:33,963 --> 00:02:40,883
meaning offering respect to others
without expecting any in return.

25
00:02:40,883 --> 00:02:47,083
He said, even those 
who are not worthy of respect,

26
00:02:47,083 --> 00:02:53,240
or, we could say, who are apparently 
not worthy of respect.

27
00:02:53,980 --> 00:03:01,520
Just as it’s easy to be tolerant, 
when things are tolerable,

28
00:03:01,991 --> 00:03:06,301
and it’s easy to be humble
in certain circumstances.

29
00:03:06,301 --> 00:03:12,741
So it’s easy to give honor to those 
who are worthy of honor,

30
00:03:12,934 --> 00:03:23,983
but it’s difficult to practice humility,
when our ego is being crushed.

31
00:03:23,983 --> 00:03:34,023
Or if we feel we are being insulted
or not recognized.

32
00:03:34,023 --> 00:03:43,672
And, the ‘taror iva sahiṣṇunā’—
even more tolerant than a tree.

33
00:03:43,672 --> 00:03:51,198
Śrīla Guru Mahārāj said that the tree …
Someone is cutting down a tree,

34
00:03:51,213 --> 00:03:53,886
and they are sawing a tree 
or chopping it down,

35
00:03:53,886 --> 00:04:01,646
and while they are doing that 
the tree is providing shade to them.

36
00:04:02,534 --> 00:04:09,544
That sort of conception of toleration 
is being invoked.

37
00:04:09,544 --> 00:04:16,284
That in the midst of being assaulted, 
attacked, dealt with unfairly,

38
00:04:16,284 --> 00:04:20,424
whatever the case might be, 
the heading might be,

39
00:04:20,458 --> 00:04:24,818
still offering shade, shelter.

40
00:04:26,463 --> 00:04:31,645
Like we see sometimes children 
on the lap of the mother,

41
00:04:31,645 --> 00:04:37,973
they’re kicking the mother
or they are doing things

42
00:04:37,973 --> 00:04:40,623
that if you were older 
it would be objectionable.

43
00:04:40,627 --> 00:04:44,376
But they are being tolerated 
because of love and affection.

44
00:04:44,376 --> 00:04:52,565
And, like what did Gurudev 
compare it to also?

45
00:04:52,565 --> 00:04:57,775
He said, “Stool being passed.”

46
00:04:57,775 --> 00:05:01,832
Sometimes they are passing stool 
on the parent.

47
00:05:01,832 --> 00:05:05,905
That is not a case 
for getting rid of the child.

48
00:05:05,905 --> 00:05:08,905
[Laughing]
He said so,

49
00:05:08,905 --> 00:05:12,598
but he used this in the context 
of the guru and the disciple.

50
00:05:12,628 --> 00:05:18,458
Devotee will think,
“Uh, Kṛṣṇa is in the background,

51
00:05:18,463 --> 00:05:22,119
for some reason 
He is letting me hear something

52
00:05:22,119 --> 00:05:28,984
or observe something
for my own internal correction.

53
00:05:28,984 --> 00:05:35,627
I am not here to correct others,
I’m here to correct myself.

54
00:05:35,627 --> 00:05:39,803
And Gurudev said himself 
once too, “I am thinking,

55
00:05:39,803 --> 00:05:45,068
if someone is doing wrong, 
but they are sincere,

56
00:05:45,068 --> 00:05:47,899
then I am thinking 
that they’re getting inspiration

57
00:05:47,899 --> 00:05:50,419
for internal correction.”

58
00:05:50,419 --> 00:06:00,569
So he is delaying correcting them.
Thinking they are a sincere person,

59
00:06:00,569 --> 00:06:07,357
they’re hearing the voice chaitya-guru 
within their conscience—

60
00:06:07,357 --> 00:06:13,515
chaitya-guru by extensions 
and getting the inspiration for

61
00:06:13,725 --> 00:06:16,025
inner correction.

62
00:06:17,445 --> 00:06:22,035
So, again, my religion—
finding fault with myself.

63
00:06:22,041 --> 00:06:23,200
That we can do.

64
00:06:23,200 --> 00:06:25,980
Guru Mahārāj said sometimes

65
00:06:25,980 --> 00:06:28,980
quoting the observations 
of another men,

66
00:06:28,980 --> 00:06:29,980
summarizing saying:

67
00:06:29,980 --> 00:06:32,787
“What is the message 
of the Bhagavad-gītā?”

68
00:06:32,787 --> 00:06:42,300
“Don’t quarrel with the environment,
correct yourself, heal thyself.”

69
00:06:42,840 --> 00:06:53,490
So, that’s our position, 
but what we find intolerable

70
00:06:53,496 --> 00:07:02,732
is the blasphemy of other devotees.
Not ourselves.

71
00:07:02,732 --> 00:07:06,152
That we can tolerate 
and think it is deserved.

72
00:07:06,152 --> 00:07:13,188
But of other devotees, Kṛṣṇa; 
that is the first offense to the Holy Name.

73
00:07:13,188 --> 00:07:16,566
The very first.

74
00:07:16,566 --> 00:07:23,084
Kṛṣṇa won’t tolerate that, 
and so we don’t tolerate that either.

75
00:07:23,084 --> 00:07:28,356
If we can’t do anything about it— 
we withdraw from the situation.

76
00:07:28,646 --> 00:07:33,430
As Saraswatī Ṭhākur 
said in Rādhā Kuṇḍa,

77
00:07:33,430 --> 00:07:36,412
“If I was just here
doing my own bhajan, 
 

78
00:07:36,412 --> 00:07:39,412
and someone said 
something unfortunate,

79
00:07:39,412 --> 00:07:42,823
I would just withdraw from there,
and I wouldn’t make an issue about it.

80
00:07:42,823 --> 00:07:47,843
But I am here in the role 
as an Acharya, so I have to.”

81
00:07:50,566 --> 00:07:53,825
And actually, 
when Gurudev told me this, 
 

82
00:07:53,825 --> 00:07:57,825
it was … there was someone
I couldn’t tolerate.

83
00:07:57,825 --> 00:08:05,805
They were offending some other
dear devotees of Gurudev.

84
00:08:05,822 --> 00:08:11,962
But Avadhūt Mahārāj and Gurudev 
were tolerating.

85
00:08:11,962 --> 00:08:16,663
So I thought there’s something
wrong with me,
 

86
00:08:16,663 --> 00:08:19,663
so I am going to try 
and adjust myself.

87
00:08:19,663 --> 00:08:21,347
Because I’ve got Gurudev 
and Avadhūt Mahārāj, 
 

88
00:08:21,347 --> 00:08:24,272
and they are tolerating,
but I can’t tolerate,

89
00:08:24,272 --> 00:08:27,892
so I’m going to adjust 
and be like them.

90
00:08:27,892 --> 00:08:31,822
So I met with this person 
and readjusted myself,

91
00:08:31,822 --> 00:08:35,576
and I was very proud,
and happy of myself,

92
00:08:35,576 --> 00:08:38,451
and I couldn’t wait, 
and when Gurudev came in,

93
00:08:38,451 --> 00:08:41,891
and I’m so proud, 
like a peacock,

94
00:08:41,891 --> 00:08:44,310
and then I said, “Mahārāj”,
and he said, “Yeah?”

95
00:08:44,310 --> 00:08:49,810
I said, “Now I am also seeing 
that person like you and Avadhūt Mahārāj,

96
00:08:49,810 --> 00:08:53,363
the way you are seeing,
I am also seeing like that,

97
00:08:53,363 --> 00:08:56,173
I’ve changed my position.”

98
00:08:56,499 --> 00:08:58,815
Like, aren’t I a good boy?

99
00:08:58,815 --> 00:09:03,104
And Gurudev looked at me,
and he goes, “I can never say that.”

100
00:09:03,104 --> 00:09:05,814
[Laughing]

101
00:09:05,814 --> 00:09:11,154
And I’m like, what? 
I thought that …

102
00:09:11,188 --> 00:09:16,958
And that’s when he said,
“Finding fault with Vaiṣṇavas …”

103
00:09:16,958 --> 00:09:19,954
and he went through the whole list 
“… this is intolerable!”

104
00:09:19,954 --> 00:09:22,446
And he said,
“My religion is finding fault with myself,

105
00:09:22,446 --> 00:09:26,616
not casting blame on others,
the environment …”

106
00:09:27,521 --> 00:09:33,041
That’s why, ultimately, 
who are we trying to please?

107
00:09:33,041 --> 00:09:38,710
And this is the part that is easy to say,
but the bitter pill to swallow.

108
00:09:38,710 --> 00:09:42,007
We’re trying to please Kṛṣṇa
and His devotees.

109
00:09:42,007 --> 00:09:44,532
And the ultimate devotee,
Rādhārāṇī, says,

110
00:09:44,532 --> 00:09:52,672
“If pleasing them involves Me 
being unhappy on any level,

111
00:09:52,686 --> 00:09:58,020
I’m OK with that. 
I want them to be happy.”

112
00:09:58,020 --> 00:10:02,240
So that’ll be our consideration:
sādhu, sāstra, guru, Vaiṣṇav.

113
00:10:02,240 --> 00:10:04,692
What is ‘them’?

114
00:10:04,692 --> 00:10:07,372
vaiṣḥnavī pratiṣṭhā, tāte koro niṣṭhā
[Vaiṣḥnava Ke?]

115
00:10:07,372 --> 00:10:09,669
What makes them happy?

116
00:10:09,669 --> 00:10:14,543
Not an egocentric way 
of viewing everything,

117
00:10:14,543 --> 00:10:17,383
but theocentric, guru‒centric.

118
00:10:18,393 --> 00:10:19,440
Hare Kṛṣṇa.

